C++:
1. RAII (resource released in destructor)
2. Exclusive ownership (only one owner)
3. Copy constructor and copy assignment deleted
4. Supports move semantics
5. get() -> returns raw pointer
6. release() -> releases ownership without deleting object
7. reset() -> replaces managed object
8. swap() -> exchanges ownership
9. operator bool() -> checks for nullptr
10. Destructor uses delete, so this version supports T but not T[] arrays.

A unique_ptr is a lightweight RAII smart pointer that provides exclusive ownership of a 
dynamically allocated resource and transfers ownership through move semantics while preventing copying.
